name: bacon
notes: |
  Temps are Breville Control Freak pan-surface settings.
  Works in stainless or seasoned (cast iron / carbon steel) — both render evenly; seasoned holds
  heat better and needs no added fat. On stainless a splash of oil to start stops sticking before
  the fat renders.
  Save the rendered fat for the eggs (see breakfast/fried-eggs and breakfast/scrambled-eggs).
steps:
  - set pan to 130°C (go as low as 120°C for a gentler, more even render — the fat needs to melt out before the lean crisps)
  - lay bacon into the pan as it warms so the fat renders gradually (don't drop onto a screaming pan)
  - turn at least every few mins
  - should take 12-20 mins to render to your liking (longer the lower you go)
  - for crispier bacon, nudge up to 160-170°C toward the end
